dc_description_s: AMS 1. North Decimal Degree 22.716667. South Decimal Degree 22.666667. East Decimal Degree 120.316667. West Decimal Degree 120.250000. Alternate title: Toshien. In upper left margin: Formosa city plans 1:10,000. Polyconic projection. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals. Compiled in 1944 from aerial photography dated September and August 1944, by photo-planimetric method and by reference to Formosa 1:50,000, A.M.S. Sheet 2115-II, 1944. Target Chart No. 28, 14th U.S.A.A.F., 3 Feb. 1944. Additional information from intelligence data. Place names are transcribed according to the Modified Hepburn (Romaji) System. With a glossary. Name has been changed to Tso-ying [Tsoying].
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
